      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:2:49:4",
      "text": [
        " لَا يَجُوزُ طَلَاقُ الْمَرِيضِ وَ يَجُوزُ نِكَاحُهُ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Humeyd Bin Ziyad, from Ibn sama’at, from Abdullah Bin Jabala, from Ibn Bukeyr, from Ubeyd Bin Zurara, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The divorce of the sick (man) is not allowed, but his marriage is allowed’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "4. Humayd ibn Ziyad has narrated from ibn Sama‘ah from ‘Abd Allah ibn Jabalah from ibn Bukayr from ‘Ubayd ibn Zurarah who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘One’s divorcing during his illness is not permissible, however, his marriage is permissible.’” "
        ]
      }
